18
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 27=

19
00:01:57,580 --> 00:01:58,660
Isn't this my laptop?

20
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:03,700
You helped me
play that video last night?

21
00:02:06,460 --> 00:02:08,540
Have you figured out
how to thank me?

22
00:02:13,260 --> 00:02:14,980
When did you start

23
00:02:15,380 --> 00:02:16,820
knowing my exact plan?

24
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:20,660
And when did you

25
00:02:20,660 --> 00:02:21,900
steal my laptop

26
00:02:22,311 --> 00:02:23,733
and do all this behind my back?

27
00:02:24,577 --> 00:02:25,980
Did you overhear my conversation

28
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:27,100
with Wang Ruohai?

29
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:28,740
The flash drive I gave him,

30
00:02:28,860 --> 00:02:29,700
was it with you?

31
00:02:36,980 --> 00:02:37,540
What?

32
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:40,820
What are you talking about?

33
00:02:42,940 --> 00:02:45,060
You think I was eavesdropping
on you two?

34
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:46,500
Why would I do that?

35
00:02:48,980 --> 00:02:51,020
That's called foresight.

36
00:02:51,340 --> 00:02:52,340
I knew from the start

37
00:02:52,420 --> 00:02:53,820
your plan was never going to work.

38
00:02:55,340 --> 00:02:56,660
Good thing we had Zhao De.

39
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:58,700
Without his tech skills,

40
00:02:58,820 --> 00:03:00,955
you couldn't even have connected
to the big screen.

41
00:03:04,180 --> 00:03:05,420
Wang Ruohai this,

42
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:06,580
Wang Ruohai that.

43
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:09,020
You really put that much faith
in that coward?

44
00:03:09,940 --> 00:03:10,780
You'd rather trust him

45
00:03:11,140 --> 00:03:12,860
than your own master?

46
00:03:15,580 --> 00:03:17,340
I know you helped me.

47
00:03:18,420 --> 00:03:19,500
I just don't know why.

48
00:03:22,140 --> 00:03:23,420
I don't feel like

49
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:27,260
thanking you.

50
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:28,620
I'm not sure it's you

51
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:29,420
or just me.

52
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:30,260
I can't figure it out.

53
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,420
Don't be mad.

54
00:04:06,620 --> 00:04:07,500
Listen.

55
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:10,020
Don't think everything's fine

56
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:11,333
just because you're back at work.

57
00:04:11,660 --> 00:04:12,700
You know Fang Yun.

58
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:13,780
The more useful you are,

59
00:04:14,044 --> 00:04:15,540
the more secure your position is.

60
00:04:16,244 --> 00:04:17,340
Once you're upstairs,

61
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:19,060
she'll ask what your next step is,

62
00:04:20,133 --> 00:04:21,210
so she can take the credit.

63
00:04:21,210 --> 00:04:21,860
Got it?

64
00:04:22,540 --> 00:04:24,460
You think every superior is like you?

65
00:04:25,540 --> 00:04:26,020
Fine.

66
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:27,511
Maybe she won't take the credit.

67
00:04:28,220 --> 00:04:29,300
But if you

68
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:30,220
haven't thought ahead,

69
00:04:30,220 --> 00:04:31,977
she'll definitely say
you don't have a plan.

70
00:04:32,022 --> 00:04:33,540
What makes you think I don't have one?

71
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:36,220
Looks like you're getting smarter.

72
00:04:36,311 --> 00:04:37,260
But not consistently.

73
00:04:45,340 --> 00:04:45,860
Shiyu.

74
00:04:47,420 --> 00:04:48,540
When you were little,

75
00:04:50,580 --> 00:04:52,300
I didn't spend enough time with you.

76
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,820
I failed you.

77
00:04:56,940 --> 00:04:58,340
You had to face

78
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,177
all those growing pains by yourself.

79
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:02,380
Dad,

80
00:05:03,020 --> 00:05:04,220
don't blame yourself.

81
00:05:04,620 --> 00:05:06,140
It's all behind me now.

82
00:05:06,340 --> 00:05:07,500
I only brought it up today

83
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:08,780
because

84
00:05:08,940 --> 00:05:10,420
when I was at my lowest,

85
00:05:11,155 --> 00:05:13,020
Wang Ruohai was the one
who pulled me through.

86
00:05:14,460 --> 00:05:15,340
He encouraged me.

87
00:05:16,180 --> 00:05:18,860
He gave me hope again.

88
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:21,260
That's when

89
00:05:21,460 --> 00:05:22,700
I fell for him.

90
00:05:24,740 --> 00:05:27,460
So after you finished your master's,

91
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:28,860
you insisted on coming back

92
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:30,340
because of him?

93
00:05:32,580 --> 00:05:32,980
Yes.

94
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:36,020
It's just a shame.
We were meant to meet,

95
00:05:36,780 --> 00:05:38,220
but not meant to stay together.

96
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:40,460
Does Wang Ruohai know

97
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:41,860
you came back for him?

98
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:46,460
Shiyu,

99
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:48,460
if you'd told him,

100
00:05:49,020 --> 00:05:50,540
maybe he wouldn't have left you.

101
00:05:52,260 --> 00:05:53,140
There's no point.

102
00:05:54,460 --> 00:05:56,860
Even if we hadn't broken up now,

103
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:58,740
it never would've lasted.

104
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:04,100
What about Qian Fei?

105
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:06,820
She's Wang Ruohai's ex-girlfriend.

106
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,980
Won't hiring her

107
00:06:09,260 --> 00:06:11,380
cause you problems?

108
00:06:13,020 --> 00:06:14,300
Why would it?

109
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:17,420
Qian Fei is capable and strategic.

110
00:06:17,660 --> 00:06:19,380
She'll help Shanlifang go public.

111
00:06:20,020 --> 00:06:21,100
As for Wang Ruohai,

112
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:24,540
he was once the light in my life.

113
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:27,460
But when it comes
to vision and ambition,

114
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:30,660
Shanlifang's future doesn't need him.

115
00:06:32,140 --> 00:06:33,060
My future

116
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,180
doesn't need him, either.

117
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:42,420
Shiyu.

118
00:06:43,180 --> 00:06:43,500
Dad.

119
00:06:44,580 --> 00:06:45,500
I'm lucky

120
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:47,900
to have a daughter like you.

121
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,660
Do you remember when you were little...

122
00:07:11,060 --> 00:07:11,820
Go on in.

123
00:07:14,940 --> 00:07:16,300
You know what to say, right?

124
00:07:19,380 --> 00:07:22,060
Now Shanlifang's asset restructuring
and financial reorganization

125
00:07:22,060 --> 00:07:23,460
have basically met the goals.

126
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:27,220
The land, assets,
and property valuations

127
00:07:27,540 --> 00:07:29,340
are also in the final stage
of verification.

128
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:31,244
We can use the attention
from this banquet

129
00:07:31,311 --> 00:07:32,140
to our advantage.

130
00:07:32,260 --> 00:07:33,020
On one hand,

131
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:35,340
it'll help repair our image.

132
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:36,410
On the other hand,

133
00:07:36,410 --> 00:07:38,577
it'll help us strengthen relationships
with key clients

134
00:07:38,688 --> 00:07:40,100
and secure larger investments.

135
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:42,020
As for other businesses...

136
00:07:43,660 --> 00:07:44,260
Very good.

137
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:45,700
Well done.

138
00:07:45,860 --> 00:07:46,980
Looks like you came prepared.

139
00:07:48,940 --> 00:07:50,140
Alright. Let's go with that.

140
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:51,860
Whether Shanlifang accepts it

141
00:07:52,220 --> 00:07:53,100
is up to them.

142
00:07:55,140 --> 00:07:55,660
Okay.

143
00:07:55,940 --> 00:07:57,820
(ID Badge)

144
00:07:58,020 --> 00:07:58,700
Don't be nervous.

145
00:07:59,888 --> 00:08:01,620
All you need to do
is explain it clearly.

146
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:35,180
Participate in developing
and implementing

147
00:08:35,300 --> 00:08:36,266
the quality standards.

148
00:08:36,540 --> 00:08:38,140
That's all I have to say

149
00:08:38,340 --> 00:08:39,740
about the follow-up plan.

150
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,580
Hejing's team has been

151
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:51,780
very impressive.

152
00:08:52,020 --> 00:08:53,244
Ms. Qian, you managed to gain

153
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:55,140
such a clear understanding
of the company

154
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:57,180
in such a short time.

155
00:08:57,420 --> 00:08:59,300
We're very impressed.

156
00:08:59,460 --> 00:09:01,060
Please review and discuss

157
00:09:01,260 --> 00:09:02,900
Ms. Qian's proposals
as soon as possible.

158
00:09:03,940 --> 00:09:05,660
If PR and Publicity

159
00:09:05,660 --> 00:09:07,060
have nothing to add,

160
00:09:07,111 --> 00:09:09,088
let's move forward with implementation.

161
00:09:09,420 --> 00:09:11,460
Especially the PR teams

162
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:12,500
and department heads.

163
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:14,340
Start carrying out
your assignments immediately.

164
00:09:14,420 --> 00:09:15,500
Keep the outsourced work

165
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:17,180
strictly confidential.

166
00:09:17,340 --> 00:09:18,060
We'll arrange

167
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:20,060
a coordination meeting
as soon as possible.

168
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:23,340
Ms. Qian, anything else to add?

169
00:09:23,820 --> 00:09:24,500
Nothing from me.

170
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,020
Thank you.

171
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:27,460
Alright. Thanks, everyone.

172
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:28,740
That's all for today.

173
00:09:28,860 --> 00:09:30,700
Meeting adjourned.

174
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:36,060
Not bad.

175
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:37,380
You've improved a lot.

176
00:09:39,740 --> 00:09:40,660
A year ago,

177
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:42,020
you looked like an amateur

178
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:43,260
in front of Liao Shiyu.

179
00:09:44,060 --> 00:09:44,940
Now

180
00:09:45,100 --> 00:09:46,660
you're able to go toe-to-toe

181
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:47,820
with her.

182
00:09:51,820 --> 00:09:53,140
I'm really curious

183
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:55,580
who turned you into
the person you are now.

184
00:09:57,260 --> 00:09:58,340
You, of course.

185
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:02,980
I didn't teach you flattery.

186
00:10:06,420 --> 00:10:08,380
I think you already know the answer.

187
00:10:15,770 --> 00:10:17,790
ظآزWhat matters to meظآز

188
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:21,470
ظآزIs what you needظآز

189
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:29,530
ظآزNo more, no less.
I only hope I can give it to youظآز

190
00:10:30,310 --> 00:10:32,100
ظآزWhat I treasureظآز

191
00:10:33,660 --> 00:10:36,860
ظآزIs what I haveظآز

192
00:10:37,888 --> 00:10:40,088
What are you doing?
Why did you plug in that flash drive?

193
00:10:40,380 --> 00:10:42,700
Stop watching dramas. Study.

194
00:10:44,180 --> 00:10:45,420
These are my personal notes

195
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:47,420
from years of running projects.

196
00:10:47,940 --> 00:10:48,740
Study well.

197
00:10:49,911 --> 00:10:51,340
There you go, acting all mature again.

198
00:10:51,555 --> 00:10:52,740
Fine. Give it back.

199
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:53,860
Don't move.

200
00:10:53,911 --> 00:10:55,060
Finger Flick Technique.

201
00:10:56,380 --> 00:10:57,260
Childish.

202
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:00,340
Let's see if you've got what it takes.

203
00:11:00,350 --> 00:11:02,244
Who knows whether
you'll actually learn anything.

204
00:11:02,340 --> 00:11:05,100
ظآزAnd words I can't make sense ofظآز

205
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:07,740
(I'm not freeloading. I polished
your report. Consider us even.)

206
00:11:07,740 --> 00:11:12,300
ظآزDreams, nonsense,
and the words hidden in my heartظآز

207
00:11:12,622 --> 00:11:14,980
Leaving your post during work hours
without permission?

208
00:11:15,140 --> 00:11:16,180
Who gave you the nerve?

209
00:11:17,420 --> 00:11:18,980
You're my special assistant now.

210
00:11:19,377 --> 00:11:21,220
You're expected to be on call
during work.

211
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:22,740
Keep your phone on at all times.

212
00:11:23,044 --> 00:11:24,540
Don't you know something that basic?

213
00:11:25,740 --> 00:11:26,620
I need you on call

214
00:11:26,780 --> 00:11:27,980
so Ms. Fang and I

215
00:11:28,140 --> 00:11:29,140
can reach you anytime.

216
00:11:30,020 --> 00:11:31,940
From now on,
if it's not part of your job,

217
00:11:32,020 --> 00:11:32,820
don't get involved.

218
00:11:33,940 --> 00:11:35,900
I owe everyone an apology.

219
00:11:36,660 --> 00:11:37,860
The materials I prepared

220
00:11:38,060 --> 00:11:38,580
were...

221
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:39,380
I took them.

222
00:11:40,820 --> 00:11:42,300
Sorry. I forgot to give them to you.

223
00:11:42,300 --> 00:11:46,420
ظآزHolding hands
and walking at a steady paceظآز

224
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:48,630
ظآزWhat I long forظآز

225
00:11:54,300 --> 00:11:55,620
(Yeah.)

226
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:58,140
(Why would he be worried about me?)

227
00:11:59,540 --> 00:12:01,220
(Since I met him,)

228
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:04,500
(he's helped me revise my reports,
gone to Sichuan with me,)

229
00:12:05,780 --> 00:12:07,660
(guided me at work,)

230
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,380
(and even stood up for me.)

231
00:12:10,380 --> 00:12:14,370
ظآزTruths, lies,
and words said for appearancesظآز

232
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:18,020
ظآزLeaving me feeling like
I'm walking on airظآز

233
00:12:18,020 --> 00:12:18,860
(Could it be...)

234
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:22,660
(It can't be. I'm overthinking it.)

235
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,700
(He just sees me as his landlady.)

236
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:28,260
(Still, I'm lucky
to have a friend like him),

237
00:12:28,260 --> 00:12:30,020
(someone who's always)

238
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:31,380
(looking out for me.)

239
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:33,260
(And my flight ticket home, too.)

240
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:36,860
(I really need
to thank Li Yifei for that.)

241
00:12:38,580 --> 00:12:43,180
ظآزThose sweet promises and words of loveظآز

242
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:50,060
Another ugly photo of you.

243
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:50,900
Look.

244
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:52,820
I've gotten approval

245
00:12:53,340 --> 00:12:54,660
from Ms. Fang

246
00:12:54,755 --> 00:12:55,820
to head home two days early

247
00:12:55,866 --> 00:12:56,977
from the Chinese New Year.

248
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,140
I haven't thought about that yet.

249
00:13:00,580 --> 00:13:01,380
It's because

250
00:13:01,380 --> 00:13:03,288
the flight you booked for me
leaves earlier now.

251
00:13:03,580 --> 00:13:04,740
If I couldn't change it,

252
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:06,044
I wouldn't be able to get home.

253
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:07,180
So I had no choice

254
00:13:07,222 --> 00:13:09,311
but to ask for leave
right after coming back to work.

255
00:13:10,860 --> 00:13:12,340
Getting full of yourself.

256
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:14,740
Taking advantage of the situation.

257
00:13:15,380 --> 00:13:15,940
What?

258
00:13:18,220 --> 00:13:18,780
Nothing.

259
00:13:26,540 --> 00:13:27,100
Qian Fei,

260
00:13:27,620 --> 00:13:28,700
I actually wanted to say...

261
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:30,980
You were going
to congratulate me, right?

262
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:31,940
How about this?

263
00:13:32,180 --> 00:13:34,340
I'll buy groceries tonight

264
00:13:34,660 --> 00:13:35,700
and cook you a good meal.

265
00:13:35,820 --> 00:13:36,860
I'm grateful to you,

266
00:13:36,980 --> 00:13:38,580
my Li Yifei, Young Master Li,

267
00:13:38,740 --> 00:13:40,311
my wonderful master, and my best buddy,

268
00:13:40,355 --> 00:13:42,220
for always encouraging me
and helping me.

269
00:13:43,620 --> 00:13:44,460
Wonderful master?

270
00:13:45,580 --> 00:13:46,380
Best buddy?

271
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:47,580
Of course.

272
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:50,060
Just like Yu and Jingjing,

273
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:52,460
you're all very important to me.

274
00:13:52,780 --> 00:13:54,340
I'm really grateful

275
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:55,460
to have you all

276
00:13:55,540 --> 00:13:56,500
in my life.

277
00:14:00,140 --> 00:14:00,660
Fine.

278
00:14:01,740 --> 00:14:03,740
Seeing how sincerely

279
00:14:03,740 --> 00:14:04,900
you're thanking me,

280
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:07,700
I'll accept your gratitude.

281
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,060
Hurry up and tell me
what you want for dinner.

282
00:14:10,220 --> 00:14:10,888
Anything's fine.

283
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:14,180
Nothing in particular.

284
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:16,380
You have no appetite?

285
00:14:16,580 --> 00:14:17,060
No.

286
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:19,340
I mean,

287
00:14:19,780 --> 00:14:20,620
I'll eat

288
00:14:21,066 --> 00:14:21,900
whatever you make.

289
00:14:24,860 --> 00:14:26,060
Aww, I'm touched.

290
00:14:27,540 --> 00:14:28,540
Cut it out.

291
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:31,380
That doesn't suit us.

292
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:34,020
Come on.

293
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:35,266
What do you want for dinner?

294
00:14:35,555 --> 00:14:37,688
You're not going to make me treat you
to a feast?

295
00:14:38,820 --> 00:14:39,900
Premium sea urchin.

296
00:14:42,540 --> 00:14:44,220
Jun has been acting

297
00:14:44,220 --> 00:14:45,660
pretty normal lately, right?

298
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:46,340
Yeah.

299
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:47,220
Maybe

300
00:14:47,380 --> 00:14:49,140
they've talked things out

301
00:14:50,020 --> 00:14:52,020
and agreed to stay friends.

302
00:14:52,380 --> 00:14:53,220
That's a good thing.

303
00:14:53,220 --> 00:14:53,940
Miss Yu.

304
00:14:54,340 --> 00:14:55,740
Look, it's them again.

305
00:14:59,380 --> 00:15:00,180
Dang.

306
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:02,900
It's really her.

307
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:19,700
(Restroom)

308
00:15:24,020 --> 00:15:24,820
Restroom?

309
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,500
Me too.

310
00:15:29,466 --> 00:15:30,180
Please go ahead.

311
00:15:35,980 --> 00:15:36,740
You see,

312
00:15:37,140 --> 00:15:37,660
if Jun

313
00:15:38,060 --> 00:15:40,780
really cleared things up with Dang Yu,

314
00:15:41,620 --> 00:15:43,060
why hasn't he moved back home?

315
00:15:44,940 --> 00:15:46,140
Maybe he still hasn't

316
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:49,060
gotten over her.

317
00:15:51,740 --> 00:15:54,060
Anyway, my bottom line

318
00:15:54,660 --> 00:15:55,900
is that he marries someone local.

319
00:15:56,060 --> 00:15:57,860
I'm not considering
anyone from out of town.

320
00:15:57,860 --> 00:15:58,660
I agree.

321
00:15:58,660 --> 00:15:59,340
She has to be

322
00:15:59,340 --> 00:16:01,620
someone decent, like Dang.

323
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:02,500
Exactly.

324
00:16:05,780 --> 00:16:06,580
Mr. and Mrs. Jun.

325
00:16:10,820 --> 00:16:11,300
Dang.

326
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:11,940
Uh.

327
00:16:12,580 --> 00:16:13,580
What a coincidence.

328
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:15,060
- Yeah.
- What a small world.

329
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:16,380
We just...

330
00:16:16,555 --> 00:16:18,020
We had dinner and went for a walk.

331
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:19,100
Yeah. We're taking a walk.

332
00:16:20,866 --> 00:16:22,380
Seeing each other once or twice a day

333
00:16:22,380 --> 00:16:23,540
is a coincidence.

334
00:16:24,340 --> 00:16:26,820
But three times.
It starts to look like stalking.

335
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:29,300
No way. I'd never stalk you.

336
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:29,860
Exactly.

337
00:16:30,020 --> 00:16:30,420
No.

338
00:16:30,660 --> 00:16:32,780
If Jun

339
00:16:32,780 --> 00:16:34,260
found out,

340
00:16:34,420 --> 00:16:35,980
he'd cut me off.

341
00:16:36,660 --> 00:16:37,620
Don't worry.

342
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:39,740
He'd never do that.

343
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:43,020
We've talked things through.

344
00:16:43,340 --> 00:16:45,260
From now on, we're just friends.

345
00:16:46,220 --> 00:16:47,140
Did you two talk?

346
00:16:47,260 --> 00:16:47,740
Friends?

347
00:16:49,940 --> 00:16:51,420
Mr. and Mrs. Jun, I'll get going.

348
00:16:55,860 --> 00:16:57,100
This girl's impressive.

349
00:16:58,020 --> 00:16:59,380
She works so hard in Shanghai,

350
00:16:59,380 --> 00:17:00,650
and she's juggling several jobs.

351
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:01,740
She's driven.

352
00:17:02,844 --> 00:17:04,460
You don't see many Shanghai girls

353
00:17:05,620 --> 00:17:06,500
working this hard.

354
00:17:06,660 --> 00:17:09,100
I mean, because she's from out of town.

355
00:17:09,340 --> 00:17:10,380
If she doesn't work hard,

356
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:12,700
how else is she supposed to make it?

357
00:17:14,020 --> 00:17:15,500
If only she were

358
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:16,740
a Shanghai local.

359
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:37,340
Why aren't you at work?

360
00:17:38,780 --> 00:17:39,940
Aren't you going home today?

361
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:42,580
What's that got to do with you?

362
00:17:45,620 --> 00:17:46,940
Don't be so ungrateful.

363
00:17:47,311 --> 00:17:48,940
I'm offering to take you to the airport

364
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:50,044
and help with your luggage.

365
00:17:50,066 --> 00:17:51,340
Shouldn't you be moved to tears

366
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:52,540
and thanking me?

367
00:17:53,911 --> 00:17:55,220
I'll give you another chance.

368
00:17:56,380 --> 00:17:57,500
Adjust your mood.

369
00:17:57,688 --> 00:17:59,060
Give me the right reaction.

370
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:01,740
You're taking me to the airport?

371
00:18:03,311 --> 00:18:04,577
Since when are you so nice?

372
00:18:05,940 --> 00:18:07,500
Is it purely a humanitarian concern?

373
00:18:10,060 --> 00:18:11,260
Why do I feel a little scared?

374
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:13,220
What's there to be afraid of?

375
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:16,180
You're being too nice.

376
00:18:16,180 --> 00:18:16,860
It's weird.

377
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:19,780
Something's fishy.

378
00:18:21,540 --> 00:18:22,180
Fire away.

379
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:23,500
What do you want from me?

380
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:27,580
I know.

381
00:18:29,022 --> 00:18:30,940
Were you planning to wait
until I wasn't home

382
00:18:31,088 --> 00:18:32,930
and bring your
influencer girlfriend here

383
00:18:32,940 --> 00:18:34,288
to spend the Chinese New Year?

384
00:18:35,288 --> 00:18:36,460
What influencer girlfriend?

385
00:18:40,460 --> 00:18:41,300
You mean Jin?

386
00:18:42,140 --> 00:18:43,620
She's not my girlfriend at all.

387
00:18:43,620 --> 00:18:44,780
I don't have a girlfriend.

388
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:46,911
You're still denying it?
Still making excuses?

389
00:18:47,260 --> 00:18:49,540
Honestly, if I can put up
with living with you,

390
00:18:49,820 --> 00:18:50,940
what else can't I overlook?

391
00:18:51,980 --> 00:18:52,620
Still,

392
00:18:52,820 --> 00:18:53,940
a friendly reminder for you.

393
00:18:54,140 --> 00:18:55,660
Clean up after yourselves.

394
00:18:55,820 --> 00:18:56,933
Don't leave the place a mess.

395
00:18:56,977 --> 00:18:58,140
Or I'll be coming after you.

396
00:18:58,140 --> 00:18:59,140
Stop talking nonsense.

397
00:18:59,860 --> 00:19:01,860
Why do you always make things up?

398
00:19:02,780 --> 00:19:04,220
I'm just trying to do something nice.

399
00:19:04,230 --> 00:19:06,100
You can't even go home
for the Chinese New Year.

400
00:19:06,380 --> 00:19:08,060
I figured I'd give you two
some alone time.

401
00:19:10,980 --> 00:19:12,500
Hey. It hurts!

402
00:19:14,940 --> 00:19:15,820
I'm leaving.

403
00:19:16,940 --> 00:19:17,620
I'll take you.

404
00:19:21,060 --> 00:19:21,540
Wait...

405
00:19:22,644 --> 00:19:24,500
I just want to take you
to the airport.

406
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:25,500
No ulterior move.

407
00:19:32,820 --> 00:19:33,540
What's

408
00:19:33,540 --> 00:19:34,620
in your suitcase?

409
00:19:34,620 --> 00:19:36,740
Why is it so heavy?
My arm's about to fall off.

410
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:38,580
You insisted on carrying it.

411
00:19:38,740 --> 00:19:39,620
I didn't ask you to.

412
00:19:39,940 --> 00:19:40,620
Fine.

413
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,580
I asked for it. Serves me right.

414
00:19:42,580 --> 00:19:43,060
Happy now?

415
00:19:45,540 --> 00:19:46,940
You've got to please your girlfriend

416
00:19:46,940 --> 00:19:48,622
while carrying luggage
for your landlady.

417
00:19:48,644 --> 00:19:49,460
Life's not easy.

418
00:19:49,580 --> 00:19:51,060
For the last time,

419
00:19:51,220 --> 00:19:52,460
Jin is not my girlfriend.

420
00:19:53,666 --> 00:19:55,700
You're flirting with her
and still denying it?

421
00:19:57,740 --> 00:19:58,860
When did I flirt with her?

422
00:19:59,488 --> 00:20:01,700
We're just friends.
Can't friends help each other out?

423
00:20:02,020 --> 00:20:02,820
Fine.

424
00:20:03,180 --> 00:20:04,540
As your friend,

425
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:06,020
let me say one more thing.

426
00:20:06,140 --> 00:20:07,600
You don't have to explain yourself.

427
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:10,140
Oh, right.

428
00:20:11,340 --> 00:20:12,940
I overheard you telling your friend

429
00:20:13,140 --> 00:20:14,420
that your dad wanted a drink.

430
00:20:15,980 --> 00:20:17,540
A friend gave me two bottles of baijiu.

431
00:20:17,540 --> 00:20:18,380
I don't drink them.

432
00:20:18,540 --> 00:20:19,300
They're in the back.

433
00:20:19,420 --> 00:20:20,688
Take them home for your dad.

434
00:20:22,660 --> 00:20:24,220
Are you giving them to my dad?

435
00:20:26,580 --> 00:20:27,220
Wait.

436
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:29,420
I only asked you to pretend

437
00:20:29,660 --> 00:20:30,820
to be my boyfriend

438
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:31,860
on the phone.

439
00:20:32,111 --> 00:20:34,060
Now you're making it
feel a little too real.

440
00:20:41,660 --> 00:20:43,300
Just worry about yourself.

441
00:20:52,220 --> 00:20:53,700
Stop showing off.

442
00:20:54,580 --> 00:20:56,100
I'm busy. Talk to you later.

443
00:20:57,940 --> 00:20:59,380
If you have something to do, go ahead.

444
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,500
It's fine. It's Jun.

445
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:04,500
You said, "Stop showing off."

446
00:21:04,644 --> 00:21:06,600
Is there something going on
between Yu and him?

447
00:21:06,740 --> 00:21:07,540
No way.

448
00:21:07,540 --> 00:21:08,511
Not with his mom around.

449
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,260
But, you've got to admit,

450
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:11,740
Jun knows

451
00:21:11,740 --> 00:21:12,620
how to pursue Yu.

452
00:21:13,980 --> 00:21:14,820
You think so?

453
00:21:15,780 --> 00:21:17,780
They haven't gotten anywhere,

454
00:21:17,940 --> 00:21:19,100
but I think

455
00:21:19,220 --> 00:21:20,540
he's won her over.

456
00:21:21,380 --> 00:21:22,460
Really?

457
00:21:22,620 --> 00:21:23,380
Of course.

458
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:24,380
Because he's sincere.

459
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:25,580
Sincere?

460
00:21:26,460 --> 00:21:26,860
Hi.

461
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:27,460
Hi.

462
00:21:30,333 --> 00:21:32,133
There are bottles of liquor
in this suitcase.

463
00:21:32,140 --> 00:21:33,540
Please put a "Fragile" sticker on it.

464
00:21:33,555 --> 00:21:34,044
Sure.

465
00:21:39,660 --> 00:21:40,980
Now that I've taken your gift,

466
00:21:41,220 --> 00:21:42,460
you're not going to make me do

467
00:21:42,660 --> 00:21:44,460
something terrible for you, are you?

468
00:21:45,460 --> 00:21:46,780
Get over yourself.

469
00:21:46,844 --> 00:21:47,933
Stop saying nonsense.

470
00:21:48,420 --> 00:21:49,780
I never said

471
00:21:49,780 --> 00:21:50,940
they were for you.

472
00:21:51,220 --> 00:21:52,180
I made it pretty clear.

473
00:21:52,180 --> 00:21:52,980
They're for your dad.

474
00:21:54,740 --> 00:21:56,100
Then you're not going to make my dad

475
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:57,700
do something terrible for you, are you?

476
00:21:58,780 --> 00:22:00,620
I am. Just wait.

477
00:22:02,060 --> 00:22:02,540
Thank you.

478
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:06,380
What did you mean
by "things are looking up"?

479
00:22:07,220 --> 00:22:08,540
My landlady said

480
00:22:08,860 --> 00:22:10,540
things aren't over
between you and Dang Yu.

481
00:22:33,755 --> 00:22:35,620
(I know. I told you before.
You need to open up.)

482
00:22:35,620 --> 00:22:37,950
(The most important thing
when pursuing a girl is sincerity.)

483
00:22:46,260 --> 00:22:47,020
Mr. Jun,

484
00:22:47,220 --> 00:22:48,540
sorry to keep you waiting.

485
00:22:48,550 --> 00:22:49,060
Not at all.

486
00:22:49,060 --> 00:22:50,180
I've been busy these days.

487
00:22:50,340 --> 00:22:51,180
Have a seat.

488
00:22:51,820 --> 00:22:54,020
My mom mentioned

489
00:22:54,020 --> 00:22:55,740
the district is holding
a dance competition.

490
00:22:56,060 --> 00:22:57,660
But hearing what you said,

491
00:22:57,660 --> 00:22:59,580
the subdistrict office wants

492
00:22:59,580 --> 00:23:03,060
to form a dance team that
combines hip-hop and square dancing.

493
00:23:03,060 --> 00:23:03,500
Yes.

494
00:23:03,780 --> 00:23:04,860
Take a look.

495
00:23:06,460 --> 00:23:07,540
The community dance team

496
00:23:07,740 --> 00:23:08,900
is mostly seniors.

497
00:23:09,066 --> 00:23:11,100
The office feels
that it doesn't really reflect

498
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:12,100
the community's energy

499
00:23:12,220 --> 00:23:13,220
or sense of togetherness.

500
00:23:13,620 --> 00:23:14,940
So they came up

501
00:23:15,140 --> 00:23:16,340
with this idea.

502
00:23:17,060 --> 00:23:18,180
We're hoping

503
00:23:18,180 --> 00:23:19,500
your studio can help us out.

504
00:23:19,860 --> 00:23:21,460
We only need two instructors.

505
00:23:21,555 --> 00:23:22,460
There'll be a subsidy.

506
00:23:23,660 --> 00:23:25,460
The schedule's a little tight.

507
00:23:25,780 --> 00:23:27,180
We'll take care of the dancers.

508
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:31,060
It's just that our instructors

509
00:23:31,260 --> 00:23:32,980
are fully booked.

510
00:23:34,580 --> 00:23:35,220
How about this?

511
00:23:35,220 --> 00:23:36,260
I'll do it.

512
00:23:36,666 --> 00:23:37,940
As for the other instructor,

513
00:23:38,100 --> 00:23:39,620
I'll have to ask her first.

514
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:41,220
Great. That's wonderful.

515
00:23:41,220 --> 00:23:42,460
Alright. Come with me.

516
00:23:42,460 --> 00:23:42,900
Sure.

517
00:23:45,260 --> 00:23:45,500
Come.

518
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:51,380
(Taekwondo Room)

519
00:23:51,780 --> 00:23:52,860
Lower your stance.

520
00:23:53,060 --> 00:23:53,780
Chest.

521
00:23:54,180 --> 00:23:55,740
Forward. Back.

522
00:23:55,900 --> 00:23:56,580
Forward.

523
00:23:56,580 --> 00:23:57,740
Miss Yu's still teaching.

524
00:23:57,740 --> 00:23:58,460
Just wait a minute.

525
00:23:58,644 --> 00:23:59,380
Adjust your stance.

526
00:24:01,540 --> 00:24:02,740
Lower your center.

527
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,860
Now reach toward my hand.

528
00:24:04,860 --> 00:24:06,180
Forward. Back.

529
00:24:06,620 --> 00:24:08,060
Forward. Back.

530
00:24:08,300 --> 00:24:09,260
Forward.

531
00:24:11,155 --> 00:24:12,850
Have some water.
I'll be right back later.

532
00:24:12,860 --> 00:24:13,140
Okay.

533
00:24:17,466 --> 00:24:18,460
What are you doing here?

534
00:24:19,140 --> 00:24:19,980
Do you always

535
00:24:20,060 --> 00:24:22,100
have this much
physical contact in class?

536
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:24,140
What's it to you? Why do you care?

537
00:24:24,420 --> 00:24:25,644
He was obviously trying to

538
00:24:25,688 --> 00:24:26,780
get you to touch him.

539
00:24:26,780 --> 00:24:28,500
Why didn't you throw him
over your shoulder?

540
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:29,380
You only ever threw me.

541
00:24:29,980 --> 00:24:30,740
Are you insane?

542
00:24:30,740 --> 00:24:31,620
He's dancing.

543
00:24:31,780 --> 00:24:32,660
Why would I throw him?

544
00:24:33,140 --> 00:24:33,940
Dancing?

545
00:24:34,380 --> 00:24:35,900
Just be more careful.

546
00:24:36,420 --> 00:24:37,460
So what are you doing here?

547
00:24:38,660 --> 00:24:39,420
Why am I doing here?

548
00:24:42,020 --> 00:24:43,180
Mr. Jun

549
00:24:43,180 --> 00:24:44,580
came to ask us for a favor.

550
00:24:44,780 --> 00:24:46,660
The district is holding
a dance competition.

551
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:50,780
They want to combine
hip-hop with square dancing,

552
00:24:50,940 --> 00:24:52,500
and they want us to teach the seniors.

553
00:24:56,540 --> 00:24:57,900
The girl has long legs.

554
00:24:58,020 --> 00:24:58,980
Can she dance?

555
00:24:58,980 --> 00:25:00,140
She's pretty good.

556
00:25:00,140 --> 00:25:01,580
Recruit her. Get her over here.

557
00:25:01,580 --> 00:25:02,820
Young people have a good spirit.

558
00:25:03,220 --> 00:25:05,700
One, two, three, four.

559
00:25:05,700 --> 00:25:07,020
Lean this way.

560
00:25:07,020 --> 00:25:08,220
Ready.

561
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:11,020
One, two, three, four.

562
00:25:11,020 --> 00:25:12,810
Your arms.

563
00:25:12,810 --> 00:25:14,140
Twist your body.

564
00:25:14,300 --> 00:25:16,620
Use your waist.

565
00:25:16,620 --> 00:25:18,260
Good. A little lower. Lower your arms.

566
00:25:18,460 --> 00:25:19,220
Nice.

567
00:25:19,380 --> 00:25:20,580
You're improving.

568
00:25:20,580 --> 00:25:22,380
Good. Don't raise your hands too high.

569
00:25:22,820 --> 00:25:23,860
Keep it up, everyone.

570
00:25:23,860 --> 00:25:24,940
Let's win the competition.

571
00:25:25,140 --> 00:25:26,100
Was that Jun?

572
00:25:26,340 --> 00:25:27,060
Yeah. That was Jun.

573
00:25:27,460 --> 00:25:28,420
He left?

574
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:30,300
Your son's busy.

575
00:25:30,580 --> 00:25:32,100
He's out recruiting hip-hop dancers.

576
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:37,860
They want other dance styles, too?

577
00:25:38,140 --> 00:25:40,300
They want more variety.

578
00:25:40,540 --> 00:25:41,900
They're expanding the hip-hop team.

579
00:25:42,340 --> 00:25:45,620
They've picked the hip-hop instructors.

580
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:46,860
My daughter

581
00:25:46,980 --> 00:25:48,540
and Yu from their studio.

582
00:25:50,020 --> 00:25:50,780
Dang Yu?

583
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:01,420
It's not that I care about the baijiu.

584
00:26:02,020 --> 00:26:02,860
I'm happy because

585
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:06,140
Li cares a lot about you.

586
00:26:08,220 --> 00:26:08,780
Really?

587
00:26:10,020 --> 00:26:11,420
Trust my judgment.

588
00:26:14,260 --> 00:26:15,500
You've never even met him,

589
00:26:15,700 --> 00:26:16,980
and you're so confident?

590
00:26:18,140 --> 00:26:19,260
Show me a picture of him.

591
00:26:20,177 --> 00:26:21,380
I'm unpacking my things.

592
00:26:22,620 --> 00:26:23,620
Then I'll take your phone.

593
00:26:26,140 --> 00:26:26,980
Hey!

594
00:26:30,740 --> 00:26:31,700
Hold on.

595
00:26:31,860 --> 00:26:32,940
Let me see if I have one.

596
00:26:39,622 --> 00:26:41,288
I don't think we've taken any photos.

597
00:26:44,020 --> 00:26:45,700
Tell him to take one now
and send it to you.

598
00:26:50,180 --> 00:26:51,020
I think I do have one.

599
00:26:51,780 --> 00:26:52,380
One second.

600
00:27:01,140 --> 00:27:02,060
Let me find it.

601
00:27:07,020 --> 00:27:07,580
Here it is.

602
00:27:09,900 --> 00:27:10,420
It's him.

603
00:27:13,820 --> 00:27:14,620
This young man

604
00:27:15,180 --> 00:27:15,940
isn't exactly

605
00:27:17,020 --> 00:27:18,100
handsome.

606
00:27:20,260 --> 00:27:22,380
He looks like that stand-up comedian

607
00:27:22,620 --> 00:27:24,380
who's popular.

608
00:27:26,060 --> 00:27:26,700
Does he?

609
00:27:30,460 --> 00:27:30,940
Fei,

610
00:27:32,380 --> 00:27:34,260
is Li really your boyfriend?

611
00:27:35,020 --> 00:27:36,100
Are you fooling me?

612
00:27:37,020 --> 00:27:38,780
Why would I do that?

613
00:27:40,622 --> 00:27:42,222
Young people these days don't date

614
00:27:42,244 --> 00:27:44,220
without taking a single photo together.

615
00:27:44,888 --> 00:27:46,340
Are you trying to get me off your back?

616
00:27:56,380 --> 00:27:58,420
Jun, why are you back?

617
00:27:59,380 --> 00:27:59,980
Mom,

618
00:28:00,540 --> 00:28:01,570
can you please

619
00:28:01,570 --> 00:28:02,940
stop bothering Dang Yu?

620
00:28:02,940 --> 00:28:04,540
You're making things awkward for her.

621
00:28:04,540 --> 00:28:05,940
I've told you so many times.

622
00:28:05,940 --> 00:28:07,620
I'll handle my own love life.

623
00:28:07,940 --> 00:28:08,980
I don't want her

624
00:28:09,140 --> 00:28:10,980
to think I'm a mama's boy, okay?

625
00:28:12,740 --> 00:28:14,860
Watch your tone! How can
you talk to your mom like that?

626
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:17,540
You finally come home,

627
00:28:17,622 --> 00:28:19,466
and the first thing you do
is upset your mom?

628
00:28:19,660 --> 00:28:20,660
What was that about?

629
00:28:21,460 --> 00:28:22,340
Come here. Sit.

630
00:28:24,888 --> 00:28:26,060
There are a few things

631
00:28:26,060 --> 00:28:27,020
I need to clear up.

632
00:28:30,300 --> 00:28:32,700
Stop saying "mama's boy".

633
00:28:33,180 --> 00:28:34,660
Do you know what that means?

634
00:28:36,060 --> 00:28:37,380
A mama's boy

635
00:28:37,380 --> 00:28:38,990
is someone who only listens to his mom,

636
00:28:39,020 --> 00:28:41,260
thinks she's always right,

637
00:28:41,260 --> 00:28:43,060
and gets spoiled by her.

638
00:28:45,140 --> 00:28:46,100
Think about it, Jun.

639
00:28:47,100 --> 00:28:48,380
Ever since high school,

640
00:28:48,580 --> 00:28:49,820
has your mom forced you

641
00:28:49,820 --> 00:28:50,980
to make a choice?

642
00:28:51,980 --> 00:28:53,100
Wasn't every decision

643
00:28:53,100 --> 00:28:55,500
made after thinking about

644
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:58,620
what was best for you
and respecting what you wanted?

645
00:29:01,300 --> 00:29:03,580
All she has wanted is for you

646
00:29:03,700 --> 00:29:05,060
to be healthy and happy,

647
00:29:05,060 --> 00:29:06,100
my son.

648
00:29:11,460 --> 00:29:12,060
Of course,

649
00:29:12,740 --> 00:29:13,420
in this family,

650
00:29:13,660 --> 00:29:15,500
she puts you in front of everything.

651
00:29:16,220 --> 00:29:17,020
If you think

652
00:29:17,020 --> 00:29:18,060
that makes you a mama's boy,

653
00:29:18,300 --> 00:29:20,100
I'm sorry to tell you,

654
00:29:20,500 --> 00:29:22,900
most sons would be mama's boys, too.

655
00:29:33,333 --> 00:29:34,977
What are you doing? Don't come over.

656
00:29:35,088 --> 00:29:36,380
What are you doing? Don't touch me.

657
00:29:36,540 --> 00:29:37,940
What are you doing? Don't touch me.

658
00:29:38,140 --> 00:29:39,060
Mom.

659
00:29:39,060 --> 00:29:40,940
I was wrong.

660
00:29:40,940 --> 00:29:41,900
Go away.

661
00:29:41,900 --> 00:29:43,700
I was wrong. My bad.

662
00:29:44,460 --> 00:29:45,620
Your mom isn't doing this

663
00:29:45,940 --> 00:29:48,180
to help Dang Yu.

664
00:29:49,980 --> 00:29:50,980
Then why?

665
00:29:51,180 --> 00:29:52,620
You ask me why?

666
00:29:53,540 --> 00:29:57,260
The subdistrict office
is holding a dance challenge

667
00:29:57,420 --> 00:29:59,940
between the square dance team
and the hip-hop team.

668
00:30:00,180 --> 00:30:01,300
So I thought

669
00:30:01,300 --> 00:30:02,900
that if Dang Yu is going to compete,

670
00:30:03,100 --> 00:30:05,180
I'd better start practicing.

671
00:30:05,180 --> 00:30:06,020
Exactly.

672
00:30:06,980 --> 00:30:08,740
Mom, you don't actually think

673
00:30:08,940 --> 00:30:10,860
you're competing against Dang Yu's team?

674
00:30:11,060 --> 00:30:11,820
Then what's it?

675
00:30:13,540 --> 00:30:15,100
You're on the same team.

676
00:30:15,177 --> 00:30:16,140
How could it be possible?

677
00:30:16,140 --> 00:30:17,860
Two different dance styles

678
00:30:18,220 --> 00:30:19,860
in one team.

679
00:30:21,580 --> 00:30:22,940
What's that supposed to be?

680
00:30:22,940 --> 00:30:24,220
Wouldn't it look ridiculous?

681
00:30:24,300 --> 00:30:25,060
Seriously.

682
00:30:25,060 --> 00:30:26,940
Mom, that's where you've got it wrong.

683
00:30:27,060 --> 00:30:28,066
That's exactly what shows

684
00:30:28,088 --> 00:30:30,460
understanding and acceptance
between different generations.

685
00:30:30,660 --> 00:30:31,300
Yes.

686
00:30:31,580 --> 00:30:33,220
It's a creative idea.

687
00:30:37,300 --> 00:30:38,660
Say, Dad, Mom.

688
00:30:38,940 --> 00:30:39,820
There's something else

689
00:30:39,820 --> 00:30:40,860
I wanted to tell you.

690
00:30:41,288 --> 00:30:43,133
I'm planning to
spend the Chinese New Year

691
00:30:43,820 --> 00:30:45,420
at Dang Yu's place.

692
00:30:45,740 --> 00:30:46,540
No.

693
00:30:46,740 --> 00:30:47,060
No!

694
00:30:47,060 --> 00:30:47,860
No way.

695
00:30:47,860 --> 00:30:48,580
No way!

696
00:30:48,580 --> 00:30:49,540
It's not going to happen.

697
00:30:49,540 --> 00:30:51,844
You can't spend the Chinese New Year
at her place.

698
00:30:57,580 --> 00:30:58,540
Hear me out first.

699
00:30:58,900 --> 00:31:00,020
I'm going to Yunnan,

700
00:31:00,300 --> 00:31:01,420
and it's all for you.

701
00:31:02,180 --> 00:31:02,820
Think about it.

702
00:31:03,060 --> 00:31:04,460
Yunnan has beautiful scenery

703
00:31:04,660 --> 00:31:06,220
and lots of ethnic minority cultures.

704
00:31:06,620 --> 00:31:07,580
I'll film

705
00:31:07,780 --> 00:31:09,580
some local customs while I'm there.

706
00:31:09,866 --> 00:31:11,133
Then, when you compete,

707
00:31:11,244 --> 00:31:12,940
we can play the footage
in the background.

708
00:31:13,088 --> 00:31:14,980
It'll look amazing
and score you extra points.

709
00:31:15,177 --> 00:31:16,700
You'll have the grand prize in the bag.

710
00:31:17,100 --> 00:31:18,860
And if my superior is happy,

711
00:31:19,060 --> 00:31:20,260
maybe it'll earn me

712
00:31:20,260 --> 00:31:21,220
some credit at work.

713
00:31:21,500 --> 00:31:22,300
Don't you think so?

714
00:31:47,620 --> 00:31:48,460
Why are you here?

715
00:31:49,740 --> 00:31:51,820
I was told someone needed help,

716
00:31:52,260 --> 00:31:53,820
so I came.

717
00:31:54,620 --> 00:31:55,420
Just so we're clear,

718
00:31:55,660 --> 00:31:56,420
I'm going to Yunnan

719
00:31:56,580 --> 00:31:58,420
to shoot background footage

720
00:31:58,420 --> 00:32:00,260
for the dance competition.

721
00:32:00,311 --> 00:32:01,822
The subdistrict office approved it.

722
00:32:03,820 --> 00:32:04,860
Helping you deal

723
00:32:04,933 --> 00:32:07,100
with your parents and relatives
asking about marriage

724
00:32:07,100 --> 00:32:08,100
is just a bonus.

725
00:32:09,066 --> 00:32:10,666
Besides, I also wanted to thank you

726
00:32:10,688 --> 00:32:12,990
for joining the community dance team
as our guest instructor.

727
00:32:14,420 --> 00:32:15,460
First,

728
00:32:15,555 --> 00:32:17,780
whether you go shoot videos
has nothing to do with me.

729
00:32:17,890 --> 00:32:19,266
I'm only responsible for the dancing.

730
00:32:19,700 --> 00:32:20,660
Second,

731
00:32:20,733 --> 00:32:23,200
I'm not worried about my parents
pressuring me to get married.

732
00:32:23,220 --> 00:32:24,700
I just want to shut my sister up.

733
00:32:29,300 --> 00:32:30,460
But I'm curious.

734
00:32:31,088 --> 00:32:32,466
How did your mom agree to this?

735
00:32:34,340 --> 00:32:35,620
My mom...

736
00:32:39,060 --> 00:32:41,260
I'm not going to tell you.

737
00:32:52,540 --> 00:32:54,020
Here we are. This is it.

738
00:32:54,620 --> 00:32:56,180
If you say anything stupid, you're dead.

739
00:32:56,820 --> 00:32:57,380
Alright.

740
00:32:57,700 --> 00:32:58,420
Don't worry.

741
00:33:28,180 --> 00:33:30,100
Here you go, the fish.

742
00:33:30,860 --> 00:33:32,300
They're all home-cooked food.

743
00:33:33,460 --> 00:33:34,380
Jun, sit.

744
00:33:36,260 --> 00:33:37,500
Honey, let's eat.

745
00:33:37,860 --> 00:33:39,340
These are all my signature dishes.

746
00:33:41,380 --> 00:33:41,860
Dig in.

747
00:33:46,140 --> 00:33:47,540
Jun, help yourself.

748
00:33:48,380 --> 00:33:49,300
Come on. Dig in.

749
00:33:49,980 --> 00:33:51,460
Yu, get Jun some food.

750
00:33:52,980 --> 00:33:53,940
You eat, too.

751
00:34:00,300 --> 00:34:00,900
Yu,

752
00:34:01,660 --> 00:34:02,860
what does

753
00:34:02,860 --> 00:34:03,900
your new boyfriend do?

754
00:34:04,860 --> 00:34:06,460
I'm a civil servant.

755
00:34:07,100 --> 00:34:07,860
Mr. and Mrs. Dang,

756
00:34:08,140 --> 00:34:09,500
I'm a Shanghai local,

757
00:34:10,140 --> 00:34:10,980
an only child,

758
00:34:11,088 --> 00:34:13,622
my parents are healthy,
and they both have good insurance.

759
00:34:14,620 --> 00:34:15,660
An only child?

760
00:34:15,770 --> 00:34:18,320
If so, after you get married,
Yu surely won't be coming home much.

761
00:34:18,420 --> 00:34:19,044
That's alright.

762
00:34:20,260 --> 00:34:21,660
I wasn't counting on it.

763
00:34:23,740 --> 00:34:25,260
Don't worry. Yu and I

764
00:34:25,340 --> 00:34:26,940
will come back to visit you often.

765
00:34:27,740 --> 00:34:28,580
Good. Very good.

766
00:34:34,300 --> 00:34:34,900
Yu,

767
00:34:35,620 --> 00:34:37,700
weren't you single?

768
00:34:37,900 --> 00:34:39,020
How did you suddenly

769
00:34:39,020 --> 00:34:40,180
get a boyfriend?

770
00:34:40,420 --> 00:34:41,700
Have you been dating all along

771
00:34:41,700 --> 00:34:42,700
and hiding it from us?

772
00:34:43,100 --> 00:34:44,660
Why would you hide something like that?

773
00:34:44,777 --> 00:34:46,355
Afraid that we'd ask you for money?

774
00:34:47,060 --> 00:34:48,100
Why would I lie?

775
00:34:48,620 --> 00:34:49,540
Jun and I

776
00:34:50,060 --> 00:34:51,660
fell in love at first sight.

777
00:34:51,860 --> 00:34:52,980
Things moved pretty fast.

778
00:34:53,820 --> 00:34:54,460
Right, babe?

779
00:34:55,100 --> 00:34:56,180
Right.

780
00:34:56,460 --> 00:34:58,460
We really clicked.

781
00:34:58,740 --> 00:34:59,340
Nice.

782
00:34:59,940 --> 00:35:00,700
Brother-in-law,

783
00:35:00,980 --> 00:35:02,620
since you're here,

784
00:35:02,820 --> 00:35:03,980
when are you two

785
00:35:03,980 --> 00:35:05,260
getting married?

786
00:35:05,333 --> 00:35:06,330
If you're getting married,

787
00:35:06,340 --> 00:35:07,940
we'll have to talk
about the bride price.

788
00:35:08,066 --> 00:35:10,200
If she's marrying far from home,
it should be higher.

789
00:35:10,660 --> 00:35:11,900
Watch your mouth.

790
00:35:12,700 --> 00:35:13,540
I see.

791
00:35:13,900 --> 00:35:14,900
I'll leave that up to Yu.

792
00:35:14,955 --> 00:35:15,800
I'll follow her lead.

793
00:35:16,300 --> 00:35:17,060
Really?

794
00:35:17,180 --> 00:35:19,020
Regarding the bride price,

795
00:35:19,260 --> 00:35:20,580
I think we should do the math.

796
00:35:20,688 --> 00:35:22,820
I've been taking care
of Mom and Dad all these years.

797
00:35:23,060 --> 00:35:24,860
Your bride price

798
00:35:24,860 --> 00:35:26,020
should make up for that, right?

799
00:35:27,244 --> 00:35:28,340
You really want to do that?

800
00:35:28,340 --> 00:35:29,333
Fine. Let's do the math.

801
00:35:30,540 --> 00:35:32,260
I've been sending
money home every month.

802
00:35:32,500 --> 00:35:33,580
That adds up.

803
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:35,980
What about you?
How long have you been graduated?

804
00:35:36,140 --> 00:35:37,733
Why are you still living
off Mom and Dad?

805
00:35:38,980 --> 00:35:39,900
Living off them?

806
00:35:40,500 --> 00:35:41,100
I just

807
00:35:41,100 --> 00:35:42,340
haven't found the right job yet.

808
00:35:42,350 --> 00:35:43,450
Have you even looked for one?

809
00:35:43,460 --> 00:35:44,140
That's enough.

810
00:35:47,300 --> 00:35:48,460
You barely come home,

811
00:35:48,480 --> 00:35:50,620
and the moment you do,
you're fighting with your sister.

812
00:35:51,860 --> 00:35:53,940
Dad, we're not fighting.

813
00:35:54,100 --> 00:35:55,540
We're just kidding around.

814
00:35:56,340 --> 00:35:58,380
Honey, this is your favorite.

815
00:35:58,460 --> 00:35:58,820
Come.

816
00:36:00,060 --> 00:36:01,100
Mr. and Mrs. Dang,

817
00:36:01,380 --> 00:36:02,980
I know you worked hard

818
00:36:03,060 --> 00:36:04,260
to raise Yu.

819
00:36:04,660 --> 00:36:06,860
From now on, we'll take good care

820
00:36:06,860 --> 00:36:08,180
of you both.

821
00:36:08,300 --> 00:36:09,420
Good.

822
00:36:10,540 --> 00:36:11,740
You sure know what to say.

823
00:36:12,620 --> 00:36:13,220
Mr. Dang.

824
00:36:15,140 --> 00:36:16,340
Honey.

825
00:36:21,700 --> 00:36:22,580
Drink slowly, Jun.

826
00:36:24,733 --> 00:36:25,540
Eat the dishes.

827
00:36:32,620 --> 00:36:34,420
Didn't you bring Dad a gift?

828
00:36:34,500 --> 00:36:35,100
Go get it.

829
00:36:43,020 --> 00:36:43,580
Mr. Dang,

830
00:36:43,860 --> 00:36:45,540
we brought you some sea cucumber.

831
00:36:47,700 --> 00:36:49,060
That's much too expensive.

832
00:36:49,300 --> 00:36:50,860
Thank you, my good daughter.

833
00:36:50,980 --> 00:36:52,300
I didn't raise you for nothing.

834
00:36:52,660 --> 00:36:53,780
Of course, Dad.

835
00:36:53,940 --> 00:36:55,540
You worked so hard raising me.

836
00:36:55,900 --> 00:36:57,060
I know your health isn't great,

837
00:36:57,155 --> 00:36:59,200
so I wanted to get you something
to help you recover.

838
00:36:59,300 --> 00:37:00,620
Am I right, Yu?

839
00:37:03,740 --> 00:37:04,260
Thank you.

840
00:37:04,340 --> 00:37:04,955
It's nothing.

841
00:37:08,060 --> 00:37:08,740
Mr. Dang,

842
00:37:08,980 --> 00:37:10,620
it's a small gift from Yu and me.

843
00:37:18,220 --> 00:37:20,100
It may not be worth much,

844
00:37:20,260 --> 00:37:22,020
but if it helps,

845
00:37:22,180 --> 00:37:23,220
we'll bring you

846
00:37:23,220 --> 00:37:24,500
more next time.

847
00:37:25,660 --> 00:37:27,540
Jun, you're too kind.

848
00:37:27,700 --> 00:37:28,700
Not at all.

849
00:37:41,060 --> 00:37:41,980
Need a hand?

850
00:37:43,060 --> 00:37:43,900
Forget it.

851
00:37:44,020 --> 00:37:46,020
If you help,
my dad's going to lose it again.

852
00:37:51,555 --> 00:37:53,140
Where did you get all that cordyceps?

853
00:37:55,600 --> 00:37:56,880
I swiped it from my mom's cabinet

854
00:37:56,900 --> 00:37:58,220
before I left.

855
00:37:58,780 --> 00:37:59,780
I had a feeling

856
00:37:59,900 --> 00:38:00,980
it'd come in handy.

857
00:38:02,460 --> 00:38:03,100
How much was it?

858
00:38:03,688 --> 00:38:04,740
I'll pay you back later.

859
00:38:07,060 --> 00:38:08,180
No need. You can have it.

860
00:38:08,900 --> 00:38:09,700
I can't do that.

861
00:38:10,500 --> 00:38:11,300
I can't take it.

862
00:38:12,044 --> 00:38:13,300
Otherwise, how are you going

863
00:38:13,380 --> 00:38:14,444
to explain it to your mom?

864
00:38:14,860 --> 00:38:16,540
I'll tell her

865
00:38:16,700 --> 00:38:18,220
it was a necessary sacrifice

866
00:38:18,340 --> 00:38:19,380
for the dance competition.

867
00:38:19,780 --> 00:38:20,900
She'll understand.

868
00:38:20,977 --> 00:38:23,060
Your mom cares that much
about the competition?

869
00:38:24,311 --> 00:38:25,488
After the Chinese New Year,

870
00:38:25,533 --> 00:38:27,340
the office is holding
a dance competition.

871
00:38:28,060 --> 00:38:30,100
She thinks that if I do well,

872
00:38:30,260 --> 00:38:31,500
it'll help me get promoted.

873
00:38:31,980 --> 00:38:33,980
So this always takes priority

874
00:38:34,180 --> 00:38:35,140
for her.

875
00:38:36,500 --> 00:38:37,220
Sometimes,

876
00:38:38,540 --> 00:38:39,340
I kind of envy you.

877
00:38:40,900 --> 00:38:41,620
Me?

878
00:38:41,740 --> 00:38:42,660
What is there to envy?

879
00:38:46,020 --> 00:38:46,620
Jun.

880
00:38:48,700 --> 00:38:49,660
Yu, leave it.

881
00:38:49,670 --> 00:38:50,700
I'll have a chat with Jun.

882
00:38:52,700 --> 00:38:54,180
I haven't finished washing the dishes.

883
00:38:54,780 --> 00:38:55,980
It's fine. I'll do them later.

884
00:39:48,100 --> 00:39:49,333
(Qian Fei: Reunion Dinner.)

885
00:40:06,860 --> 00:40:08,360
(Make me these when you get back.)

886
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:10,280
(Jin)

887
00:40:15,820 --> 00:40:16,420
Hello?

888
00:40:16,820 --> 00:40:17,740
Fei?

889
00:40:18,140 --> 00:40:19,940
I'm filming a vlog

890
00:40:19,940 --> 00:40:21,660
on the pedestrian street
near your place.

891
00:40:22,533 --> 00:40:24,140
My stomach suddenly hurts really badly.

892
00:40:24,620 --> 00:40:26,220
Can you come help me?

893
00:40:27,700 --> 00:40:28,100
I...

894
00:40:29,980 --> 00:40:31,260
I'm busy right now.

895
00:40:32,340 --> 00:40:34,100
Call Zihao. He's got
plenty of free time.

896
00:40:34,260 --> 00:40:35,260
Have him come.

897
00:40:36,300 --> 00:40:37,620
My phone's almost dead.

898
00:40:37,620 --> 00:40:38,700
It's about to shut off.

899
00:40:39,420 --> 00:40:42,140
My stomach hurts, and I can't find
a place to rent a power bank.

900
00:40:43,380 --> 00:40:46,060
I'm right at the entrance
to the pedestrian street.

901
00:40:46,620 --> 00:40:48,140
Fei, I...

902
00:40:48,311 --> 00:40:49,340
Don't worry. You...

903
00:40:50,460 --> 00:40:51,100
Hello?

904
